This paper deals with the application of machine learning to detect malicious email attachments, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms such as deep neural networks and gradient boosted decision trees suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of predictive performance, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of classifiers on Microsoft Office documents, which could involve computer vision techniques and therefore fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
